body:
#### System information

Geth version: `GethDroid/v1.6.5-stable/android-arm/go1.8.3`
OS & Version: Android

#### Expected behaviour

In Web3.js (and javascript console), making calls on methods throwing exceptions return `false`.

From [solidity doc](http://solidity.readthedocs.io/en/develop/control-structures.html#exceptions) : `exceptions are send and the low-level functions call, delegatecall and callcode, those return false in case of an exception`

From Android wrapper through *JNI* :
* Call (with `pendingCallContract`) a smart-contract method which throws an exception, should throw a particular exception or return the default value like in web3.js. 
* Call (with `pendingCallContract`) a smart-contract method which doesn't exist at specified address, should throw another particular exception.

#### Actual behaviour

Currently, `pendingCallContract` returns `null` in two cases : 
- when an exception is thrown by a smart-contract method call.
- when the method doesn't exist in smart-contract (encoded `data` field of `CallMsg` doesn't match with any of smart-contract methods at address specified in the `to` field of `CallMsg`  )

#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour

* __Case 1 :__

In an Android app on Ropsten :

```java

Context context = Geth.newContext();

CallMsg msg = Geth.newCallMsg();
msg.setFrom(Geth.newAddressFromHex("0xe63EE5DC4c8b502B0000c773dF75339440aACa7a"));
msg.setTo(Geth.newAddressFromHex("0x5de9b726eb633f509471cde1b567f335b3040bcb"));
msg.setValue(new BigInt(0));
msg.setGas(1000000);
msg.setData(ByteString.decodeHex("b2747118").toByteArray());
msg.setGasPrice(new BigInt(1000000));

byte[] answer = client.pendingCallContract(context, msg);

```
At [`0x5de9b726eb633f509471cde1b567f335b3040bcb`](https://ropsten.etherscan.io/address/0x5de9b726eb633f509471cde1b567f335b3040bcb) i published a test contract.
Call the method which throw an exception. It's encoded call is `b2747118`

`answer` is `null`

* __Case 2 :__ 

Modify one character of previous encoded call : `b2747118` --> `d2747118`
We try to call an unknown method.

```java

Context context = Geth.newContext();

CallMsg msg = Geth.newCallMsg();
msg.setFrom(Geth.newAddressFromHex("0xe63EE5DC4c8b502B0000c773dF75339440aACa7a"));
msg.setTo(Geth.newAddressFromHex("0x5de9b726eb633f509471cde1b567f335b3040bcb"));
msg.setValue(new BigInt(0));
msg.setGas(1000000);
msg.setData(ByteString.decodeHex("d2747118").toByteArray());
msg.setGasPrice(new BigInt(1000000));

byte[] answer = client.pendingCallContract(context, msg);

```

`answer` is also `null`

I'm working on a library making geth node management and smart-contract communication easier to developers, named [Ethdroid](http://ethmobile.io/ethdroid). This issue is linked to [#31](https://github.com/ethmobile/ethdroid/issues/31) on our issue tracker
